-- Kan Cabinet's Approval Rating Falls to 2 Points to 41%, Mainichi Reports
-- Tak Kumakura
-- 2010-07-25T21:46:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/kan-cabinet-s-approval-rating-falls-to-2-points-to-41-mainichi-reports.html

          
          
             Japanese Prime Minister Naoto Kan
has an approval rating of 41 percent, according to a Mainichi
newspaper survey taken July 24-25, down 2 percentage points from
July 7-8. His disapproval rating rose 4 points to 40 percent,
the newspaper said.  
 Even so, 80 percent of the respondents said Kan should stay
in office. Kanâ€™s Democratic Party of Japan has a public support
of 30 percent, unchanged from the previous survey. The newspaper
took the survey by telephone and obtained 1,061 valid responses.  
          
          


  


        